I like it. It kinda pissed me off that people were abusing the stats on sewing kits...it makes no sense that a sewing kit be better than a backpack for carrying stuff.<P>Besides, I'm a tailor, this might throw some more life into the 10-slot bag trade...before you could give up 2 slots and ditch 2.5 stones by using a sewing kit...now the backpack will weigh around the same as the sewing kit AND have a more noticeable weight reduce (which i didnt know about) AND have the extra 2 slots.<P>And this will also fix people using racial sewing kits as containers over 10-slot bags, which is unfair to non-woodelf/halfling merchants who can't make the kits (and I'm a woodelf smith as well, so this isn't jealousy talking)<P>--------------------<P>"Do as I say, not as I do" -someone or other
