Two things really suck here:<P>- if you have low strength on your character, the weight change blows.  Consider me - carrying 4 toolboxes (0.4 * 4 = 1.6), which will now probably weigh around ten times that much.  Weight reduction of the CONTENTS doesn't mean jack if the containers themselves are overloading you.<P>- Toolboxes and sewing kits can carry GIANT sized items, whereas backpacks cannot.  Try putting your Worker's Sledgemallet in a backpack sometime and you'll see what I mean.<P>This change is a big ass nerf - make no mistake about it.
