<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Someone did ask them about this already.  Here is the post and Alan's responce.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> <B>hey guys i'd like to thank you for this ... this is definately a long overdue patch and i support it whole heartedly.<P> i would like to point out 1 thing tho... as a monk this will raise a cry of alarm. due to our weight limitations items like the tailoring kit were a way for us to stay w/in our limits, this is especially so w/ the below 30 lvls where money isnt always readily available and we are unable to go after mobs which drop some of the lighter weight reduction packs like the shralock pack. the question is, are you considering the addition of something like a monk only cure silk pack or other easily obtainable light weightcontainer w/ monks in mind<P>lonaddar greyharte<BR>lvl 46 monk </B><P> the tribunal We are certainly aware of the effect this will have on Monks. But how many packs is a Monk carrying, realistically? Not a lot of them. Just filling one ten-slot pack with relatively lightweight items is going to put you near your limit. Let's assume that the Monk is right at his limit, and all of those items fit into one tailor made container. The new container weighs about 2.2 pounds more than the tailoring kit he was using before. But with the 10% weight reduction the new container is saving him 1.4 pounds (assuming it has 14 pounds of stuff in it). So he is only losing out on about .8 pounds of carrying capacity. Admittedly, this is less of a savings the more tailoring kits you replace with tailor made packs. You have to keep one thing in mind. It's like making a character for the game Champions (for those of you familiar with Hero Systems). You don't get points for a Disadvantage unless it is actually a disadvantage. Designing a character that is afraid of little green aliens in a game world where the aliens are all huge and red isn't going to hinder the character at all. If we continue to design special items that make it easier for Monks to get past their carrying restriction, then we effectively make that restriction meaningless. There are already a lot of special items, like armor and weapons, designed specifically to be light for Monks to use. Too much more of that and the restriction isn't really a restriction anymore. This does not mean that we will not make a bag specifically for Monks. It's just not something we're going to do now.<P>Alan <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I agree with him for the most part but he did screw up on the math.  Since the backpack weighs 3 pounds you can only save approx 1.1 pounds before you reach the max for a monk.  Of course this also ignores any cash as well.
