Ok, I know I am going to get flamed for this but let's look at something realistically for a sec.<BR>I enjoyed the little "Glitch" in the game just as much as the rest of y'all. Every one of my characters carries Sewing kits and Toolboxes that I made. <BR>But let's be truthful, how realistic is it that my character can carry 8 Containers (backpacks, toolboxes, Large-sewing Kits...) even empty and fight and run. In the Army I do good carrying what little I have to.<BR>Magic Items that provide weight reduction fall in to this area to help out.<BR>I don't feel that this is a TRUE Nerf. Inconvenient yes, kinda frustrating that I will have to re think some of my actions do to weight constraints (That I had found a Sneaky Loophole around), yes.<P>We are all going to be forced to go back to the way it was intended and play within the lines again, that's all.<BR>Relax, within a month we will all find ourselves simply reminiscing about how for such a long time we got around having to worry about weight as much.<P>Just my Honest Opinion.  <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>RavenSF<BR>Lanys T'Vyl - svr<BR>Suasponte - Level 17<BR>Paladin<BR>Sincgars - Level 15 Druid<P><A HREF="http://members.fortunecity.com/meihem_maker/index.html" TARGET=_blank>Mischief ~n~ Mayhem Guild</A><P>If you don't have time to do it right, <BR>will you have time to do it again?
