<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Hmmm, so Monks don't like this (some of them at least)...shows they aren't thinking it through.<P>Someone said a Large Sewing Kit weighs in at 2.5 less then a Large Backpack...<BR>Okay, a Large Backpack that is Tailored has a 10% weight reduction for ALL items it carries...<P>Let's do some quick math.<BR>How many times have you carried around those Rusty Swords?<BR>How much do each one of those weigh?<BR>Add them all together (8 of them).<BR>Divide by 10.<BR>That is the amount of weight SAVED in using Tailored Backpacks.<P>Hmmm, 8 x 6 = 48.  Times 10% = 4.8...much better then just having a bag that is 2.5 less and still adding in those heavy items.<P>Now figure if they were 10 slots...the you would be saving 6 in weight...<P>Sure, costs a little bit (150pp I think) but, considering that I know a guy on Rodcet that GIVES you a 10 slot for every 8 HQBPs you SELL him for 30pp (going rate for HQBPs on Rodcet), and it offsets the cost..<BR>Gives you one for free, then you sell him 2 more HQBPs and you have enough plat to BUY two more 10slots...<P>Quit your whining.  This IS a good thing in the overall picture. <BR>Monks KNOW they have a weight issue when they start.  Those that don't, figure it out PDQ on their own.  <BR>So, you have to bank A LOT.  <BR>So you may have to ask a group mate (better trust them that much or you shouldn't be grouped in the first place) to carry your heavy items till you are ready to run to town.<BR>So What?  Is it really that big of a deal?  If it is, please, take the time to learn to deal WITHIN the restrictions placed on one of the better classes in the game.  I mean, I love my Monk...when I want to come home and Whomp Tuckus, that is the character I play.<P>--------------------<P>"Sleep is for the weak and those with slow internet connections" - Me
